snippet.title: From The Newsroom Podcast: Bathurst 1000 racegoers urged to get tested
snippet.description:
A school in Melbourne’s northern suburbs has closed as a precaution after a primary student tested positive to coronavirus, Bathurst 1000 racegoers and locals who live in the area are being urged to monitor for symptoms and get tested as soon as possible after COVID traces were detected in sewage, Nine people from the same family have died from food poisoning after eating homemade noodle soup that had reportedly been kept in a freezer for a year, Pope Francis has endorsed same-sex civil unions, Amber Heard could face perjury charges in Australia, Melbourne Storm captain Cameron Smith has said if he makes a decision to retire it will have nothing to do with the result in this Sunday's grand final.  

GET ALL THE LATEST NEWS AND LIFESTYLE VIDEOS: https://www.news.com.au/
